This verse translation is a parallel with that of Robert of Greatham‚ who turned the Sunday gospels and homilies into Anglo-French rhyme about 1300, and with that of the unknown north-countryman who turned them into rhyming English. The work begins and ends at the same place as the frequent Latin excerpt on the Passion, which would seem to show that the translator used one of these Passion manuscripts, and not a complete one of the whole Meditationes.
